//
// test/Lower/m3_corpus/s12/pass.test — M5 T106 / FR-030 / SC-003.
//
// **Closed at M5.** `NSLExpandVariablesPass` now walks the variable's
// enclosing region recursively (rather than only the variable's
// parent block), so the partial-assignment shape
// `v[3:0] = 0;` — which lowers to `nsl.transfer %ext, %lit` with
// `%ext = nsl.extract %v, ...` inside `nsl.func`'s body — no longer
// crashes the pipeline. The pass leaves the residual `nsl.variable`
// op in place when uses remain after the walk (full per-field /
// whole-width-concat lowering is the visitor-side follow-up
// demonstrated by `partial_assignment_S12.mlir`).
//
// RUN: %nslc -emit=mlir %S/../../../sema/s12/pass.nsl > %t.actual.mlir
